.content-grid
  .row-fluid
    .span12
      %h2
        Websites
        %small
          Powered by open data
      %p
        Most of these are works of passion. The more recent ones are contributions to the ever-growing
        %a{:href => "http://data.cityofchicago.org/"} open
        %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/#!/search/opengov%20chicago"} government
        %a{:href => "http://www.meetup.com/OpenGovChicago/"} movement
        in Chicago.
        I like to work with
        = succeed "," do
          %a{:href => "http://www.ruby-lang.org/en/"} Ruby
        %a{:href => "http://www.google.com/fusiontables"} Fusion Tables
        and
        %a{:href => "http://jquery.com/"} jQuery

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://www.sharemyshare.org"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/share-my-share.jpg", :title => "Share my Share"}/
          %h4
            Share my Share
        %p
          Do you have a weekly veggie CSA and can't pick it up this weekend? Wouldn't it be nice if you could donate your box to charity? Well now you can. Share my Share allows residents of Logan Square to feed Chicago's hungry with their extra CSA boxes.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://chicagoist.com/2012/07/25/new_website_allows_csa_buyers_to_do.php"} Chicagoist

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://crimeinchicago.org"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/crime-in-chicago.jpg", :title => "Crime in Chicago"}/
          %h4
            Crime in Chicago
        %p
          Crime in Chicago is a data visualization by
          %a{:href => "http://opencityapps.org"} Open City
          that lets you explore crime trends in Chicago's 50 wards. It was built using
          %a{:href => "https://data.cityofchicago.org/Public-Safety/Crimes-2001-to-present/ijzp-q8t2"} open data about Chicago crimes
          released by the
          = succeed "." do
            %a{:href => "http://www.cityofchicago.org/police"} Chicago Police Department
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://gov20.govfresh.com/open-city-launches-new-civic-app-to-map-crime-in-chicago/"} GovFresh

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://cpstiers.opencityapps.org"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/cps-tiers.jpg", :title => "Chicago Public School (CPS) Tiers"}
          %h4
            Chicago Public School (CPS) Tiers
        %p
          CPS places every part of the city into one of four socio-economic "tiers" and requires selective schools to reserve the same number of spots for the students from each tier. This tool helps you find which CPS tier you are in.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://blogs.edweek.org/edweek/parentsandthepublic/"} EdWeek
          |
          %a{:href => "http://www.cltv.com/videogallery/68761359/News/3/9-politics-tonight-pt-1#pl-62809047"} CLTV "Politics Tonight"
          |
          %a{:href => "http://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2012/03/09/chicago-public-school-tiers"} WTTW "Chicago Tonight"
          |
          %a{:href => "http://chicagoist.com/2012/03/08/new_web_app_makes_it_easier_for_cps.php"} Chicagoist

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://clearstreets.org"} 
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/icons/snow.png", :title => "ClearStreets - Plow Tracker"}/
          %h4
            ClearStreets
        %p
          The City of Chicago launched
          = succeed "," do
            %a{:href => "http://www.cityofchicago.org/content/city/en/depts/mayor/iframe/plow_tracker.html"} Plow Tracker
          an app that tracks the city's snow plows in real time. This app uses the same data. By knowing where the plows are, we've figured which streets have been plowed.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://chicagotonight.wttw.com/2012/01/31/chicago-data-apps"} WTTW "Chicago Tonight"
          |
          %a{:href => "http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-talk-snow-tracker-0121-20120121,0,4501133.story"} Chicago Tribune
          |
          %a{:href => "http://chicagoist.com/2012/01/20/clear_streets_a_better_use_of_snow.php#photo-1"} Chicagoist
          |
          %a{:href => "http://gridchicago.com/2012/new-plow-tracker-style-website-hits-the-web-in-time-for-todays-snow-storm/"} GridChicago

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://chicagolobbyists.org"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/chicago-lobbyists.jpg", :title => "Chicago Lobbyists"}
          %h4
            Chicago Lobbyists
        %p
          An open data, open government, and open source project intended to improve the transparency of interactions between the City of Chicago and lobbyists and their clients.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://gov20.govfresh.com/can-the-internet-help-disrupt-the-power-of-chicago-lobbyists-through-transparency/"} article on govfresh
          |
          %a{:href => "http://chicagoist.com/2011/12/07/new_web_project_simplifies_citys_op.php"} article on Chicagoist
          |
          %a{:href => "http://appsformetrochicago.com/apps/chicago-lobbyists"} Apps for Metro Chicago Contest
          |
          %a{:href => "http://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/mayor/press_room/press_releases/2011/august_2011/mayor_emanuel_announcesnewlobbyistdatathatprovidesclearconnectio.html"} City release on updated lobbyist data
          |
          %a{:href => "https://twitter.com/#!/chilobbyists"} @ChiLobbyists on Twitter

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://chicagobuildings.org"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/chicago-buildings.jpg"}
          %h4
            Vacant and Abandoned Building Finder - Chicago
        %p
          Find vacant and abandoned buildings in Chicago. Data comes from reports made for open and vacant buildings to 311 since January 1, 2010.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://gov20.govfresh.com/chicagobuildings-org-maps-vacant-and-abandoned-buildings-using-open-government-data/"} article on govfresh
          |
          %a{:href => "http://www.webitects.com/blog/post/mapping-chicagos-vacant-buildings"} Webitects blog
          |
          %a{:href => "http://appsformetrochicago.com/community_round_entries"} Apps for Metro Chicago Contest
          (7th place)

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://LookAtCook.com"}
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/screenshots/look-at-cook.jpg", :title => "Look at Cook"}
          %h4
            Look at Cook
        %p
          Budget transparency visualization for Cook County, IL displaying all county departments broken down by fund and
          control officer from 1993 to 2011. Done as a collaboration with 12th District Commissioner John Fritchey. Built with Fusion Tables and jQuery.
          %br/
          %strong Press:
          %a{:href => "http://radar.oreilly.com/2011/09/look-at-cook-gov-data-visualization.html"} Article on O'Reilly Radar
          |
          %a{:href => "http://govfresh.com/2011/09/beautiful-budgets-look-at-cook/"} Article on govfresh
          |
          %a{:href => "http://www.webitects.com/blog/post/look-at-cook-a-budget-visualization-for-cook-county-il"} Webitects blog
      

      .grid-item
        %a{:href => "http://chicagorecyclingdropoff.com"} 
          %img.img-polaroid{:src => "/images/icons/recycle.png", :title => "Chicago Recycling Dropoff"}/
          %h4
            Chicago Recycling Dropoff
        %p
          My wife
          %a{:href => "http://ayaoconnor.com"} Aya
          and I created a map of all City of Chicago recycling drop off locations. We also set up a mobile site so you can find the nearest drop off point from your current location.

